NHL EASTERN CONFERENCE FINALS: PENGUINS v DEVILS
May 17, 2001
Ivan Hlinka
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT








Q.  Not the kind of defensive effort you probably wanted to see? 

COACH HLINKA:   I think from my side, they were the better team tonight.  They didn't give us any.  We were down 2-0 and they started to control the game, and they were concentrating on the defense and to  -- you know, after that, they got some good chances, too, because we were open.  But we have to be better in our transition game.  We didn't make nothing  -- our passes, they were too slow, to the standing position, and that's really not our game.  And we have to be better, especially in this situation.  You have to, you know, move the puck very quickly and you have to put everybody to the play, and it was not working for us tonight. Thank you. 


